WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:center
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:01.110 --> 00:00:01.860
What?!

3
00:00:01.860 --> 00:00:03.480
Oden, you're leaving?!

4
00:00:03.480 --> 00:00:05.740
There'll be less trouble, but we'll miss him.

5
00:00:05.740 --> 00:00:09.360
<b>Hakumai

Wano</b>

6
00:00:07.110 --> 00:00:09.360
I hear a monster lives in Kuri.

7
00:00:09.910 --> 00:00:11.910
A demon by the name of Ashura Doji.

8
00:00:13.080 --> 00:00:15.200
Kuri is a cancer in Wano...

9
00:00:15.200 --> 00:00:17.290
Even Shogun Sukiyaki cannot control it.

10
00:00:18.080 --> 00:00:22.460
The authorities are powerless to apprehend
criminals who take refuge in Kuri.

11
00:00:22.460 --> 00:00:26.300
But they will die there anyway
if their strength is lacking.

12
00:00:26.920 --> 00:00:31.140
Such a lawless region might
as well be another country!

13
00:00:32.930 --> 00:00:36.310
Fascinating! I shall tour the land Wano!

14
00:00:37.480 --> 00:00:39.190
Take care!

15
00:00:39.190 --> 00:00:41.350
Kin! Denjiro!

16
00:00:41.350 --> 00:00:42.730
Come visit us again!

17
00:00:42.730 --> 00:00:43.900
See you!

18
00:00:43.900 --> 00:00:47.860
He comes and goes as he pleases.

19
00:00:47.860 --> 00:00:49.650
He is a free spirit.

20
00:00:49.650 --> 00:00:51.530
Lord Yasuie!

21
00:00:51.530 --> 00:00:53.660
We have a problem!

22
00:00:54.580 --> 00:00:57.120
Look at the state of his accommodations!

23
00:00:57.120 --> 00:00:59.330
What kind of lifestyle would cause this?!

24
00:00:59.330 --> 00:01:01.870
We must charge him for the repairs!

25
00:01:03.210 --> 00:01:06.460
Or we just pretend we were
struck by a natural disaster...

26
00:01:06.460 --> 00:01:09.470
My lord, you are too soft on him!

27
00:01:09.470 --> 00:01:10.680
Lord Yasuie!

28
00:01:11.590 --> 00:01:13.220
What now?

29
00:01:15.310 --> 00:01:16.680
There is money missing?

30
00:01:16.680 --> 00:01:19.850
Yes, and I am certain
it was locked in the safe!

31
00:01:20.310 --> 00:01:21.310
Um...

32
00:01:22.770 --> 00:01:25.230
It pains me to say this...

33
00:01:25.900 --> 00:01:28.480
but I witnessed the whole thing!

34
00:01:29.820 --> 00:01:32.990
Um... Lord Oden...

35
00:01:32.990 --> 00:01:35.580
tucked the money into
his inner breast pocket...

36
00:01:36.660 --> 00:01:38.490
I knew he did it!

37
00:01:38.490 --> 00:01:40.660
He bit the hands that fed him!

38
00:01:40.660 --> 00:01:41.830
This is unforgivable!

39
00:01:41.830 --> 00:01:44.500
I think Oden would have taken it openly.

40
00:01:45.840 --> 00:01:47.380
Are you sure, Orochi?

41
00:01:48.300 --> 00:01:49.760
Y-Yes! My apologies!

42
00:01:50.170 --> 00:01:53.720
I was so scared that I couldn't stop him!

43
00:02:03.650 --> 00:02:09.070
After leaving Hakumai, Oden's group continued
to cause trouble throughout Wano

44
00:02:09.070 --> 00:02:10.940
as they headed toward Kuri.

45
00:02:18.370 --> 00:02:20.580
How long are you two going to follow me?!

46
00:02:21.080 --> 00:02:22.080
Forever!

47
00:02:22.080 --> 00:02:24.290
We love you so much!

48
00:02:28.960 --> 00:02:30.210
– He looks annoyed!
– He looks annoyed!

49
00:02:33.470 --> 00:02:36.550
Hey! Why are you standing out there?

50
00:02:36.550 --> 00:02:39.010
As your retainers, we must stand guard.

51
00:02:39.010 --> 00:02:40.560
Come in, you idiots!

52
00:02:40.970 --> 00:02:42.980
– Oden!
– Oden!

53
00:02:44.270 --> 00:02:45.770
What are you doing?

54
00:02:45.770 --> 00:02:47.110
I'm keeping a logbook.

55
00:02:47.520 --> 00:02:51.940
Apparently, voyagers overseas write
in them every day on their ships.

56
00:02:52.610 --> 00:02:56.320
The following are Oden's own 
words regarding his journeys.

57
00:02:59.030 --> 00:03:03.500
<b>Ringo</b>

58
00:03:07.290 --> 00:03:11.800
In Ringo, we came across
a couple of starving brothers in rags.

59
00:03:11.840 --> 00:03:14.720
<b>Izo

Son of a Former Hanayanagi

Dance School Headmaster</b>

60
00:03:11.880 --> 00:03:14.720
<b>Kikunojo

Izo's Younger Brother</b>

61
00:03:14.720 --> 00:03:16.260
Get lost!

62
00:03:20.680 --> 00:03:24.060
They were trying to earn money
by dancing, but people were cold.

63
00:03:30.900 --> 00:03:33.030
Why are you two following me?!

64
00:03:34.940 --> 00:03:36.110
Stop eating, you brats!

65
00:03:36.110 --> 00:03:37.030
I want more.

66
00:03:37.030 --> 00:03:38.530
I said stop!

67
00:03:38.530 --> 00:03:40.200
Do not give him any more!

68
00:03:40.200 --> 00:03:43.750
They mentioned being
the heirs to a school of dance,

69
00:03:43.750 --> 00:03:47.620
but their father was arrested,
breaking up their family.

70
00:03:47.620 --> 00:03:52.800
They brazenly ate our oden,
sobbing all the while.

71
00:03:59.930 --> 00:04:02.350
<b>Kibi</b>

72
00:04:01.930 --> 00:04:08.270
In Kibi, there was a ghoul who
collected hair from the living and dead alike.

73
00:04:08.770 --> 00:04:12.940
He was a freak who made a living
selling brushes made from the hair.

74
00:04:16.360 --> 00:04:19.320
<b>Kanjuro
Ghoul of Kibi</b>

75
00:04:21.950 --> 00:04:25.620
Whoa! I give up! I give up! I give up!
I thought you were a corpse!

76
00:04:25.620 --> 00:04:30.040
I punched him for coming after my hair,
but then he began to follow me too.

77
00:04:30.040 --> 00:04:33.880
He claimed to have suffered—
and deservedly so—from persecution.

78
00:04:33.880 --> 00:04:43.300
<b>Udon</b>

79
00:04:34.710 --> 00:04:39.340
In the forest-covered Udon, there were
rumors of a notorious mountain bandit.

80
00:04:39.340 --> 00:04:43.470
They said women would be abducted,
and men would be beaten soundly.

81
00:04:44.930 --> 00:04:46.770
Why are you all following me?!

82
00:04:46.770 --> 00:04:48.430
You're telling me!

83
00:04:57.280 --> 00:04:59.030
Is that the mountain bandit?!

84
00:05:01.490 --> 00:05:02.160
Jump!

85
00:05:02.570 --> 00:05:04.450
Lord Oden!

86
00:05:04.450 --> 00:05:13.540
<b>Raizo

Former Member of

the Kozuki Clan's Oniwabanshu</b>

87
00:05:05.660 --> 00:05:13.540
The prodigious ninja, Raizo, quit the Kozuki Clan's
Oniwabanshu after a kunoichi broke his heart.

88
00:05:13.540 --> 00:05:17.920
I cannot live my life in hiding any longer!

89
00:05:23.260 --> 00:05:24.760
He looks annoyed...

90
00:05:24.760 --> 00:05:33.230
<b>Lawless Land of Kuri</b>

91
00:05:34.610 --> 00:05:39.780
<b>Ashura Doji
Strongest Monster in Kuri</b>

92
00:05:35.570 --> 00:05:37.940
Kozuki Oden has come to Kuri?

93
00:05:37.940 --> 00:05:40.070
He's the shogun's son!

94
00:05:40.070 --> 00:05:41.820
I wanna kill him myself!

95
00:05:41.820 --> 00:05:43.450
Catch him and bring him here!

96
00:05:43.450 --> 00:05:44.450
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

97
00:05:53.540 --> 00:05:57.750
Those in power... We hate them most of all!

98
00:06:00.840 --> 00:06:02.630
Where's Oden?

99
00:06:02.630 --> 00:06:04.970
He went south of here to take a dump.

100
00:06:05.300 --> 00:06:07.310
Wasn't that yesterday?

101
00:06:07.310 --> 00:06:11.680
He sometimes disappears on a whim
for one or two days, right?

102
00:06:12.390 --> 00:06:15.440
Hey, Raizo! There's a gate
to Kuri in the south!

103
00:06:15.440 --> 00:06:16.190
What?!

104
00:06:17.150 --> 00:06:22.650
Crap! I swore I'd die for him, and now
I'm late to join him on the battlefield!

105
00:06:31.700 --> 00:06:35.450
<b>Kuri</b>

106
00:06:54.310 --> 00:06:59.190
This was a place filled with the stench
of death, blood, and violence!

107
00:06:59.190 --> 00:07:00.900
It was like a different world.

108
00:07:00.900 --> 00:07:04.610
All of their bloodlust was directed toward me!

109
00:07:05.240 --> 00:07:09.620
I'll lop off your head, Kozuki Oden!

110
00:07:19.210 --> 00:07:22.080
Open up the borderless map, then

111
00:07:22.080 --> 00:07:25.280
Head for that unknown edge of the ocean

112
00:07:25.280 --> 00:07:29.670
LET’S SAIL ON right now, hoist your sails up high

113
00:07:29.670 --> 00:07:32.660
Riding on the wind

114
00:07:37.790 --> 00:07:42.000
DON’T GIVE UP, it’s time to finish what we started

115
00:07:42.190 --> 00:07:44.970
So don't you grow disheartened

116
00:07:45.280 --> 00:07:48.730
Laugh the tears away through the storm

117
00:07:48.930 --> 00:07:53.160
SHOUT IT OUT, when you feel down always remember

118
00:07:53.500 --> 00:07:55.760
That’s what your friends are there for

119
00:07:55.790 --> 00:07:57.920
Y’know there’s no point in fronting,

120
00:07:57.920 --> 00:08:01.840
your crew will always have your back

121
00:08:02.210 --> 00:08:05.940
Even in the face of utter darkness

122
00:08:06.170 --> 00:08:08.930
C’mon, BRAVE IT OUT We’ll be alright

123
00:08:09.230 --> 00:08:12.720
Together you know that we’ll never lose a fight

124
00:08:12.940 --> 00:08:15.710
Open up the borderless map, then

125
00:08:15.730 --> 00:08:18.570
Head for that unknown edge of the ocean

126
00:08:18.870 --> 00:08:23.150
All great journeys starts with a single step

127
00:08:23.220 --> 00:08:24.160
DREAMIN’ ON

128
00:08:24.160 --> 00:08:26.940
Open up the borderless map, then

129
00:08:26.940 --> 00:08:29.680
Raise the flag we swore to defend

130
00:08:29.830 --> 00:08:32.570
We’ll never stop until we’ve reached the top

131
00:08:32.640 --> 00:08:37.040
Just be true to yourself until the end

132
00:08:37.170 --> 00:08:41.880
Set sail and grab it, DREAMIN ON

133
00:08:55.180 --> 00:08:57.890
<b>Daimyo and Retainers</b>

134
00:08:57.890 --> 00:08:59.730
You're Kozuki Oden, huh?

135
00:09:02.310 --> 00:09:04.110
I have been disowned,

136
00:09:04.110 --> 00:09:06.030
so I no longer have a name!

137
00:09:06.650 --> 00:09:10.650
You can enter all you like,
but we kill any who try to leave!

138
00:09:10.650 --> 00:09:13.450
Especially samurai!

139
00:09:19.250 --> 00:09:21.580
It is so restrictive!

140
00:09:23.000 --> 00:09:27.170
How can anyone live in a place like this?!

141
00:09:27.630 --> 00:09:30.050
That's hilarious.

142
00:09:30.050 --> 00:09:34.300
You're never going to leave this place!

143
00:09:34.300 --> 00:09:36.430
No, don't even try to leave!

144
00:09:37.850 --> 00:09:39.730
"Don't even try to leave"?

145
00:09:39.730 --> 00:09:43.400
That is my least favorite rule!

146
00:09:43.400 --> 00:09:45.900
I make the rules here!

147
00:09:47.070 --> 00:09:48.110
Cut him down!

148
00:10:21.350 --> 00:10:22.850
That makes you the boss?

149
00:10:34.490 --> 00:10:37.410
– Oden!
– Oden!

150
00:10:37.740 --> 00:10:39.870
Oden!

151
00:10:41.700 --> 00:10:43.960
Look! The gate has been broken!

152
00:10:52.090 --> 00:10:55.510
How can an ass who grew up
pampered in the capital...

153
00:10:56.090 --> 00:10:59.350
understand what it's like to live in hell?!

154
00:10:59.350 --> 00:11:03.020
Is that all you really want to say?!

155
00:11:05.560 --> 00:11:06.520
Look!

156
00:11:07.900 --> 00:11:09.060
Up there!

157
00:11:19.370 --> 00:11:22.580
Oden! We're here to back you up!

158
00:11:26.460 --> 00:11:27.830
I must apologize.

159
00:11:28.250 --> 00:11:31.710
I seem to have finished up already.

160
00:11:32.340 --> 00:11:35.930
It took me an entire day and night.

161
00:11:45.100 --> 00:11:47.480
Kill me already!

162
00:11:47.480 --> 00:11:49.860
I know what the future holds anyway.

163
00:11:50.860 --> 00:11:52.820
I've got nothing to live for!

164
00:11:53.820 --> 00:11:58.030
This is the infamous Ashura Doji?!

165
00:11:58.570 --> 00:12:00.700
Hey, you guys!

166
00:12:01.030 --> 00:12:04.290
Do you still love me?

167
00:12:08.080 --> 00:12:11.790
Lend me your wisdom and strength!

168
00:12:12.590 --> 00:12:16.920
I have decided that the worthless scum here...

169
00:12:17.420 --> 00:12:20.050
need me as their king!

170
00:12:24.140 --> 00:12:26.930
<b>Flower

Capital</b>

171
00:12:32.690 --> 00:12:35.360
My lord, Shogun! Lord Oden is at it again!

172
00:12:35.780 --> 00:12:38.900
What? What did he do this time?!

173
00:12:39.820 --> 00:12:40.820
Look at this!

174
00:12:46.000 --> 00:12:47.790
That lawless Kuri...

175
00:12:49.040 --> 00:12:52.130
Only he could do this...

176
00:12:52.130 --> 00:12:54.920
Is this all true?

177
00:12:57.670 --> 00:13:02.890
Leading the roughnecks
of the bloody and hellish land of Kuri,

178
00:13:02.890 --> 00:13:10.850
Oden utilized their abundant energy
to turn the wild land into a habitable place.

179
00:13:17.940 --> 00:13:23.200
After hearing of this accomplishment,
Shogun Kozuki Sukiyaki revoked his disownment

180
00:13:23.200 --> 00:13:27.370
and bestowed upon his son
the title of daimyo of Kuri.

181
00:13:25.450 --> 00:13:32.750
<b>Reformation 
of
 Kuri</b>

182
00:13:27.370 --> 00:13:31.120
Our great Lord Oden will become
the daimyo of Kuri!

183
00:13:31.120 --> 00:13:32.500
Hooray!

184
00:13:32.500 --> 00:13:34.750
Then it'll become a full-fledged province!

185
00:13:32.750 --> 00:13:39.840
<b>Reformation 
of
 Kuri</b>

186
00:13:34.750 --> 00:13:38.260
I can't believe it! But we
stuck it out to the end!

187
00:13:39.840 --> 00:13:41.590
<b>Reformation 
of
 Kuri</b>

188
00:13:42.300 --> 00:13:43.970
Kin...

189
00:13:47.260 --> 00:13:49.850
You did it! Our beloved Oden did it!

190
00:13:49.850 --> 00:13:50.810
Hooray!

191
00:13:50.810 --> 00:13:52.440
You're amazing, Oden!

192
00:13:52.440 --> 00:13:54.150
You're finally Kuri's–

193
00:13:54.150 --> 00:13:55.270
Oden!

194
00:13:59.820 --> 00:14:00.990
Absolutely!

195
00:14:03.990 --> 00:14:06.830
Daimyo!

196
00:14:11.250 --> 00:14:12.750
– Lord Oden!
– Lord Oden!

197
00:14:19.210 --> 00:14:20.710
What is the matter, Ashura?

198
00:14:22.090 --> 00:14:23.470
I...

199
00:14:23.880 --> 00:14:27.720
have never seen peace before.

200
00:14:30.060 --> 00:14:32.310
Thank you, Oden!

201
00:14:32.770 --> 00:14:35.400
Stop it! You are creeping me out!

202
00:14:39.230 --> 00:14:41.490
You bastard!

203
00:14:42.900 --> 00:14:44.530
What're you doing?! Stop it!

204
00:14:44.530 --> 00:14:46.240
Hey!

205
00:14:46.240 --> 00:14:48.200
I said "Stop it"!

206
00:14:46.620 --> 00:14:48.200
Screw you!

207
00:14:49.080 --> 00:14:50.580
Knock it off already!

208
00:14:50.580 --> 00:14:53.500
Now, a daimyo requires retainers.

209
00:14:55.000 --> 00:14:58.790
Instead of surrounding myself
with the usual wise and sober men...

210
00:15:00.800 --> 00:15:03.050
I would rather have you all.

211
00:15:12.850 --> 00:15:15.940
Be my samurai!

212
00:15:35.370 --> 00:15:37.710
– Lord Oden!
– Lord Oden!

213
00:15:38.250 --> 00:15:39.380
S-S-Stop it!

214
00:15:39.380 --> 00:15:42.750
Your snot! Your snot!
It is dripping! Oh, it is on me!

215
00:15:42.750 --> 00:15:44.720
Stop it!

216
00:15:45.720 --> 00:15:52.510
Six years after that moment in time...
yet thirty-three years before the present day...

217
00:15:52.510 --> 00:15:58.350
across the world, disbanded members
of the legendary Rocks Pirates

218
00:15:58.350 --> 00:16:04.230
each formed a new crew, extended
their influence, and became infamous.

219
00:16:04.940 --> 00:16:11.030
<b>Kuri
Beach


Wano</b>

220
00:16:11.030 --> 00:16:13.790
What are they? Animals?

221
00:16:14.240 --> 00:16:16.710
Hairy humans?

222
00:16:19.170 --> 00:16:21.250
Deformed monsters?

223
00:16:28.220 --> 00:16:29.470
Did you get it?

224
00:16:29.470 --> 00:16:30.300
Yeah...

225
00:16:36.850 --> 00:16:40.770
In the distant past, many centuries ago,

226
00:16:41.100 --> 00:16:45.730
we minks and the samurai
of Wano's Kozuki Clan

227
00:16:46.490 --> 00:16:49.780
made a pledge to become sworn brothers.

228
00:16:50.360 --> 00:16:54.240
Damn! Wano is the worst!

229
00:16:54.240 --> 00:16:56.620
Dammit! Let me down!

230
00:16:58.080 --> 00:16:59.670
I'm a kappa!

231
00:16:59.670 --> 00:17:01.120
Which makes you a monster!

232
00:17:01.120 --> 00:17:03.750
I wish we'd never set sail!

233
00:17:03.750 --> 00:17:05.710
I wish we hadn't come here!

234
00:17:05.710 --> 00:17:09.010
This isn't how you treat brothers!

235
00:17:09.380 --> 00:17:12.260
A cat monster, dog monster, and a kappa...

236
00:17:12.260 --> 00:17:14.640
Is this beach cursed?

237
00:17:14.640 --> 00:17:15.970
Let's burn them alive!

238
00:17:19.480 --> 00:17:20.270
Don't do it!

239
00:17:25.150 --> 00:17:27.820
That is plenty of ingredients for today's oden...

240
00:17:35.580 --> 00:17:37.870
You wretches!

241
00:17:46.800 --> 00:17:49.840
You should all be ashamed!

242
00:17:48.760 --> 00:17:56.220
<b>Beef 
Tendon</b>

243
00:17:49.840 --> 00:17:53.260
You fear what is different out of ignorance!

244
00:17:53.260 --> 00:17:56.220
It is pathetic to torment such little creatures!

245
00:17:56.810 --> 00:17:58.140
Thank you...

246
00:18:00.180 --> 00:18:01.480
Farewell.

247
00:18:01.480 --> 00:18:03.480
– Don't leave us like this!
– Don't leave us like this!

248
00:18:10.990 --> 00:18:12.990
So, who are the monsters?

249
00:18:12.990 --> 00:18:14.200
They followed me.

250
00:18:16.580 --> 00:18:19.200
<b>Inuarashi


Mink</b>

251
00:18:16.870 --> 00:18:19.120
Thank you for saving us!

252
00:18:21.250 --> 00:18:22.500
It's hot!

253
00:18:22.500 --> 00:18:26.880
Between starvation, a shipwreck,
and a violent mob, we almost died!

254
00:18:22.540 --> 00:18:26.080
<b>Neko-
mamushi


Mink</b>

255
00:18:27.880 --> 00:18:28.750
Ouch!

256
00:18:28.750 --> 00:18:31.010
Hey! This is too hot to eat!

257
00:18:31.010 --> 00:18:32.420
Whoa...

258
00:18:32.420 --> 00:18:35.720
I still can't get used to seeing animals talking.

259
00:18:38.600 --> 00:18:39.890
The minks!

260
00:18:39.890 --> 00:18:42.020
My father once told me about them.

261
00:18:42.020 --> 00:18:43.190
I thought so!

262
00:18:43.190 --> 00:18:45.810
We have that symbol in our country, too!

263
00:18:45.810 --> 00:18:48.570
You-gara and our people are brothers!

264
00:18:48.570 --> 00:18:50.190
And you saved our lives!

265
00:18:50.190 --> 00:18:51.780
We were starving...

266
00:18:51.780 --> 00:18:52.650
I see...

267
00:18:52.650 --> 00:18:54.400
Eat as much as you want.

268
00:18:54.400 --> 00:18:56.320
Here's to our savior.

269
00:18:56.320 --> 00:18:57.120
Ouch!

270
00:18:57.120 --> 00:18:58.490
Don't be shy.

271
00:18:58.490 --> 00:18:59.790
You'll like the radish.

272
00:18:59.790 --> 00:19:01.830
I won't forget this favor.

273
00:19:01.830 --> 00:19:02.330
Hot!

274
00:19:02.330 --> 00:19:04.000
Try the hanpen.

275
00:19:04.670 --> 00:19:05.250
Ouch!

276
00:19:05.250 --> 00:19:05.960
The konnyaku–

277
00:19:05.960 --> 00:19:08.460
No! It's too hot to eat!

278
00:19:12.800 --> 00:19:16.010
My tongue is sensitive like a cat's!

279
00:19:16.010 --> 00:19:18.140
Bad cat!

280
00:19:18.550 --> 00:19:20.100
Hey! Wait, Cat!

281
00:19:22.720 --> 00:19:24.230
Hey, Cat!

282
00:19:24.230 --> 00:19:26.600
Oden was meant...

283
00:19:27.730 --> 00:19:30.190
to boil!

284
00:19:32.780 --> 00:19:34.360
– That's kinda cool!
– That's kinda cool!

285
00:19:36.280 --> 00:19:37.450
Tastes good to me.

286
00:19:38.240 --> 00:19:39.620
And what are you?!

287
00:19:39.620 --> 00:19:43.080
The ship my mother and I were on sank, and...

288
00:19:44.000 --> 00:19:46.620
we were cast ashore in this country.

289
00:19:46.620 --> 00:19:49.920
We asked for help, but people threw
rocks at us for being fishmen.

290
00:19:50.340 --> 00:19:54.800
My mother got hurt, so we couldn't
go back to where we came from.

291
00:19:54.800 --> 00:19:57.180
Before my mother died, she told me,

292
00:19:57.180 --> 00:19:59.430
"Fishmen suffer discrimination...

293
00:19:59.430 --> 00:20:02.310
so claim that you're a kappa."

294
00:20:07.190 --> 00:20:09.440
I'm Kawamatsu the Kappa.

295
00:20:09.060 --> 00:20:12.020
<b>Kawamatsu

"the Kappa"</b>

296
00:20:09.440 --> 00:20:11.440
I've been living off leftovers.

297
00:20:12.520 --> 00:20:17.150
Thank you for saving me
and treating me to such a delicious meal.

298
00:20:17.700 --> 00:20:19.660
I'll never forget this.

299
00:20:19.990 --> 00:20:22.450
May I eat the rest?

300
00:20:22.450 --> 00:20:25.450
Nonesense. We'll cook more,
so just wait a bit.

301
00:20:25.450 --> 00:20:28.620
No, that's not necessary. It's still edible.

302
00:20:29.960 --> 00:20:31.000
Oh no...

303
00:20:31.000 --> 00:20:33.380
I failed to express proper gratitude.

304
00:20:33.380 --> 00:20:35.880
I wasted food.

305
00:20:35.880 --> 00:20:37.590
You've grown up.

306
00:20:39.970 --> 00:20:41.720
I'm meowwy sorry, Kappa!

307
00:20:41.720 --> 00:20:43.600
I'll eat it, too!

308
00:20:45.100 --> 00:20:47.350
It's still too hot!

309
00:20:49.640 --> 00:20:51.400
What an amusing cat!

310
00:20:52.770 --> 00:20:55.860
Cat!

311
00:20:56.940 --> 00:21:01.200
There must still be creatures
out there I've never seen before.

312
00:21:01.200 --> 00:21:06.040
Meeting you all has reinvigorated
my desire to one day set sail!

313
00:21:06.040 --> 00:21:06.950
Sounds great!

314
00:21:06.950 --> 00:21:08.660
The world's a big place!

315
00:21:08.660 --> 00:21:10.460
Well then, take care!

316
00:21:13.670 --> 00:21:15.090
Let us stay here!

317
00:21:15.090 --> 00:21:16.670
Were you listening to us?!

318
00:21:16.670 --> 00:21:19.050
We have no place to go!

319
00:21:19.050 --> 00:21:22.680
All right! All right!

320
00:21:23.350 --> 00:21:25.140
Yay!

321
00:21:26.010 --> 00:21:27.270
We got more people...

322
00:21:27.270 --> 00:21:30.310
I guess you just can't reject anyone.

323
00:21:31.480 --> 00:21:34.560
That's fine and all, but we're in a bind here.

324
00:21:34.560 --> 00:21:37.570
You lent money to Orochi
without asking me again!

325
00:21:37.570 --> 00:21:39.440
Why would you help that creep?!

326
00:21:39.440 --> 00:21:40.320
You see...

327
00:21:40.320 --> 00:21:45.080
He may be independent now, but with
his ties to Yasuie, I cannot abandon him.

328
00:21:49.910 --> 00:21:53.170
Silent steps. Stealthy steps. Ninja steps.

329
00:21:53.170 --> 00:21:55.590
Understood? These are the fundamentals.

330
00:21:55.590 --> 00:21:56.750
– Okay!
– Okay!

331
00:21:56.750 --> 00:21:57.750
Let's go!

332
00:21:57.750 --> 00:21:59.630
Don't be afraid of Yasuie!

333
00:21:59.630 --> 00:22:07.010
<b>Hakumai</b>

334
00:21:59.630 --> 00:22:02.970
Silent steps. Stealthy steps. Ninja steps.

335
00:22:02.970 --> 00:22:05.930
– Silent steps. Stealthy steps. Ninja steps.
– Silent steps. Stealthy steps. Ninja steps.

336
00:22:11.140 --> 00:22:14.020
Why would you want to 
steal this much money?

337
00:22:14.020 --> 00:22:16.440
Lord Oden was broke!

338
00:22:16.440 --> 00:22:19.730
If you're gonna kill us,
just do it already, you hedgehog!

339
00:22:19.730 --> 00:22:22.900
If it'll help Lord Oden...

340
00:22:22.900 --> 00:22:26.160
I'm happy to die!

341
00:22:27.580 --> 00:22:31.750
Damn you, Oden. You certainly
know how to pick them.

342
00:22:33.870 --> 00:22:36.380
I am giving you the money
you tried to steal.

343
00:22:37.790 --> 00:22:38.550
– What?!
– What?!

344
00:22:38.550 --> 00:22:42.220
Lord Yasuie! These are Hakumai's funds!

345
00:22:42.220 --> 00:22:43.510
And...?

346
00:22:47.550 --> 00:22:50.470
You can have this too. It is yours!

347
00:22:50.470 --> 00:22:52.180
Even more money?!

348
00:22:52.180 --> 00:22:54.730
You gotta be kidding me! Is this a trap?!

349
00:22:55.980 --> 00:22:57.440
Do you love Oden?

350
00:22:59.650 --> 00:23:08.870
Then take this money, make yourselves presentable,
learn some manners, buy some books, and study!

351
00:23:10.290 --> 00:23:12.040
These don't suit us!

352
00:23:19.420 --> 00:23:20.460
I am...

353
00:23:20.460 --> 00:23:22.340
No! Speak from your stomach!

354
00:23:22.340 --> 00:23:23.510
I am...!

355
00:23:31.380 --> 00:23:34.260
<b>- Religion
- History
- Economics - Samurai
- Etiquette</b>
